{{C sharp/Navigation|Keywords|if}}

The {{C sharp|if}} keyword identifies an [[C Sharp Programming/Control#if statement|{{C sharp|if}} statement]] with the following syntax:
:''if-statement'' ::= "if" "(" ''condition'' ")" ''if-body'' ["else" ''else-body'']
:''condition'' ::= ''boolean-expression''
:''if-body'' ::= ''statement-or-statement-block''
:''else-body'' ::= ''statement-or-statement-block''

If the ''condition'' evaluates to {{C sharp/kw|true}}, the ''if-body'' executes. Curly braces ("{{C sharp|{}}" and "{{C sharp|}}}") allow the ''if-body'' to contain more than one statement. Optionally, an {{C sharp|else}} clause can immediately follow the ''if-body'', providing code to execute when the ''condition'' is ''false''. Making the ''else-body'' another {{C sharp|if}} statement creates the common ''cascade'' of {{C sharp|if}}, {{C sharp|else if}}, {{C sharp|else if}}, {{C sharp|else if}}, {{C sharp|else}} statements:

<source lang="csharp">
using System;

public class IfStatementSample
{
    public void IfMyNumberIs()
    {
        int myNumber = 5;
        if (myNumber == 4)
            Console.WriteLine("This will not be shown because myNumber is not 4.");
        else if(myNumber < 0)
        {
            Console.WriteLine("This will not be shown because myNumber is not negative.");
        }
        else if(myNumber%2 == 0)
            Console.WriteLine("This will not be shown because myNumber is not even.");
        else
        {
            Console.WriteLine("myNumber does not match the coded conditions, so this sentence will be shown!");
        }
    }
}
</source>

The boolean expression used in an {{C sharp|if}} statement typically contains one or more of the following operators:

{| border=1 align=center
!width=25|Operator
!width=|Meaning
!width=25|Operator
!width=|Meaning
|----
| < || less than || > || greater than
|----
| == || equal to || != || not equal to
|----
| <= || less than or equal to || >= || greater than or equal to
|----
| && || and || <nowiki>||</nowiki> || or
|----
| ! || not
|}

See also [[C Sharp Programming/Keywords/else|{{C sharp|else}}]].

